  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist?\r\nTo allow implementing custom bound contract calls\r\nWhat are the use-cases?\r\nI want to implement `BoundContractWithRetry` that keeps retrying on errors and also switches the node URL when the current node returns too many errors.\r\nThe problem is that at the moment all generated bindings use `*bind.BoundContract` and switching it to an interface will allow using custom `BoundContract` call logic\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\nyes\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\nyes",
